Description: Double-barrel handle of Koan pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.200, 62. Rather than the rare name Tychios, this is probably part of the known Koan stamp Eutychidas (or its abbreviation). As Petrie only notes one stamp the piece is probably not to be equated with the double-stamped 1955,0920.115.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0099)
